description:
Pre-existing bug, unrelated to custom-connectors PR. Mobile users have had no bottom nav since commit fc688e5 (2025-12-02, design-system overhaul PR #94).

Repro: viewport 375x812, authenticated, /dashboard. Expected: bottom MobileNav with Home/Settings/Admin. Actual: only the desktop Header at the top with icon-only buttons (Bell = Settings is there but unlabeled; users don't recognize it). document.querySelectorAll('nav').length == 0 confirms MobileNav is never in the DOM.

Root cause: frontend/src/components/MobileNav.tsx:17-20

  const hiddenPaths = ['/', '/sign-in', '/sign-up', '/waitlist', '/changelog'];
  if (hiddenPaths.some(path => location.pathname.startsWith(path))) {
    return null;
  }

Every path starts with '/'. So '/dashboard'.startsWith('/') is true and the component returns null on every page in the app.

Fix: split exact-match (just '/') from prefix-match (the auth/waitlist/changelog subtrees).

  if (location.pathname === '/') return null;
  if (['/sign-in', '/sign-up', '/waitlist', '/changelog'].some(p => location.pathname.startsWith(p))) {
    return null;
  }

Three lines. Standalone PR against main, not bundled with custom-connectors.
